{"title_page": "Den\u00e9e Benton", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Den\u00e9e Benton\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1991|12|31}}\n| birth_place  = Eustis, Florida\n| death_date  = \n| death_place  = \n| education   = [[Carnegie Mellon University]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Fine Arts|BFA]])}}\n| occupation  = Actor, singer\n| years_active = 2014\u2013present\n| spouse        = {{marriage|[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6802489/ Carl Lundstedt]|January 2, 2020}}\n}}\n'''Den\u00e9e Benton''' (born December 31,1991) her parents are Jackie and Derryl Benton, she is an American actor and singer. Benton is best known for her [[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical|Tony]]-nominated performance as [[Natasha Rostova]] in the 2016 musical ''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812|Natasha, Pierre, & The Great Comet of 1812]]'' on Broadway.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/people/Denee-Benton/|title=Denee Benton Theatre Credits|website=www.broadwayworld.com|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref><ref name='Playbill'>{{cite web |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/get-to-know-broadways-natasha-newcomer-denee-benton |title=Get to Know Broadway\u2019s Natasha, Newcomer Den\u00e9e Benton |last1=Gioia |first1=Michael |last2= |first2= |date=29 Jul 2016 |website=Playbill |publisher= |access-date=22 Aug 2016 |quote=The actress, who played Natasha...at Boston\u2019s American Repertory Theater this past winter, has been chosen to reprise her performance for Broadway...}}</ref>\n\nBenton assumed the role of [[Elizabeth Schuyler Hamilton|Eliza Hamilton]] in the Broadway production of [[Hamilton (musical)|''Hamilton'']], beginning performances on October 30, 2018.<ref name=\"Broadway.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.broadway.com/buzz/193555/denee-benton-carvens-lissaint-to-join-the-cast-of-broadways-hamilton/|title=Den\u00e9e Benton & Carvens Lissaint to Join the Cast of Broadway's Hamilton|work=Broadway.com|access-date=2018-10-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBenton attended [[Trinity Preparatory School]] in [[Winter Park, Florida]], before graduating from [[Carnegie Mellon University]] in 2014.<ref name='Playbill'/>\n\n==Career==\nHer first break was being cast as Nabulungi in the West End and U.S. national tour of ''[[The Book of Mormon (musical)|The Book of Mormon]]''. Later she was cast in the titular role of Natasha in ''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812]]'' with the [[American Repertory Theatre]]; she made her [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut when that show opened at the [[Imperial Theatre]] on November 14, 2016.<ref name='Playbill'/> She appeared on ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]'' on December 12, 2016 to discuss the role.\n\nOn television she is best known for her featured role on the second season of the [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] series, ''[[Unreal (TV series)|UnREAL]]''.<ref name='Vulture'>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2016/08/unreal-denee-benton-on-why-ruby-is-important.html|title=UnREAL\u2019s Den\u00e9e Benton on Why a Character Like Ruby Is Important and Representation in Hollywood |last1=Basti\u00e9n |first1=Angelica Jade |last2= |first2= |date=10 Aug 2016 |website=Vulture |publisher= |access-date=22 Aug 2016}}</ref><ref name='Deadline'>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/01/monica-barbaro-denee-benton-cast-unreal-season-2-lifetime-1201692977/ |title=\u2018UnReal\u2019: Monica Barbaro, Den\u00e9e Benton & More Join Season 2 Cast On Lifetime |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |last2= |first2= |date=29 Jan 2016 |website=Deadline Hollywood |publisher= |access-date=22 Aug 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn October 17, 2018, it was announced that Benton would assume the role of [[Elizabeth Schuyler Hamilton|Eliza Hamilton]] in the Broadway production of [[Hamilton (musical)|''Hamilton'']], beginning performances on October 30.<ref name=\"Broadway.com\"/>\n\n== Theatre credits ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year(s)\n!Production\n!Role\n!Location\n!Category\n|-\n|rowspan=2 |2014\u201315\n|rowspan=2 |''[[The Book of Mormon (musical)|The Book of Mormon]]''\n|rowspan=2 |Nabulungi\n|N/A\n|U.S. National Tour\n|-\n|[[Prince of Wales Theatre]]\n|West End\n|-\n|2015\u201316\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Natasha Rostova]]\n|[[American Repertory Theater]]\n|Regional, Pre-Broadway\n|-\n|2016\u201317\n|[[Imperial Theatre]]\n|Broadway\n|-\n|2017\n| ''[[Of Thee I Sing]]''\n| Mary Turner\n| [[Carnegie Hall]]\n|MasterVoices Concert\n|-\n|2018\u201319\n|[[Hamilton (musical)|''Hamilton'']]\n|[[Elizabeth Schuyler Hamilton|Eliza Hamilton]]\n|[[Richard Rodgers Theatre]]\n|Broadway\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2013\n|''The Narrative of Dalvin Reynolds''\n| Felicia \n| Short film \n|-\n|2018\n|''Mother's Milk''\n|Lark\n| \n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Friend (film)|The Friend]]''\n| Charlotte\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Unreal (TV series)|UnREAL]]''\n|Ruby Carter\n|10 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[imdbtitle:8004684|25]]''\n| Morgan\n| Television film \n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2017\n|[[Tony Award]]\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical|Best Actress in a Musical]] \n| rowspan=3\" |''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Drama League Award]]\n|Distinguished Performance\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Theatre World Award]]\n| {{win|Honoree}}\n|\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|5715289}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Benton, Denee}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Florida]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American musical theatre actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Winter Park, Florida]]\n[[Category:Carnegie Mellon University alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Theatre World Award winners]]\n\n\n{{US-theat-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Den\u00e9e Benton\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1991|12|31}}\n| birth_place  = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place  = \n| education   = [[Carnegie Mellon University]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Fine Arts|BFA]])}}\n| occupation  = Actor, singer\n| years_active = 2014\u2013present\n| spouse        = {{marriage|[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6802489/ Carl Lundstedt]|January 2, 2020}}\n}}\n'''Den\u00e9e Benton''' (born December 31, 1992) is an American actor and singer. Benton is best known for her [[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical|Tony]]-nominated performance as [[Natasha Rostova]] in the 2016 musical ''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812|Natasha, Pierre, & The Great Comet of 1812]]'' on Broadway.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/people/Denee-Benton/|title=Denee Benton Theatre Credits|website=www.broadwayworld.com|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref><ref name='Playbill'>{{cite web |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/get-to-know-broadways-natasha-newcomer-denee-benton |title=Get to Know Broadway\u2019s Natasha, Newcomer Den\u00e9e Benton |last1=Gioia |first1=Michael |last2= |first2= |date=29 Jul 2016 |website=Playbill |publisher= |access-date=22 Aug 2016 |quote=The actress, who played Natasha...at Boston\u2019s American Repertory Theater this past winter, has been chosen to reprise her performance for Broadway...}}</ref>\n\nBenton assumed the role of [[Elizabeth Schuyler Hamilton|Eliza Hamilton]] in the Broadway production of [[Hamilton (musical)|''Hamilton'']], beginning performances on October 30, 2018.<ref name=\"Broadway.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.broadway.com/buzz/193555/denee-benton-carvens-lissaint-to-join-the-cast-of-broadways-hamilton/|title=Den\u00e9e Benton & Carvens Lissaint to Join the Cast of Broadway's Hamilton|work=Broadway.com|access-date=2018-10-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBenton attended [[Trinity Preparatory School]] in [[Winter Park, Florida]], before graduating from [[Carnegie Mellon University]] in 2014.<ref name='Playbill'/>\n\n==Career==\nHer first break was being cast as Nabulungi in the West End and U.S. national tour of ''[[The Book of Mormon (musical)|The Book of Mormon]]''. Later she was cast in the titular role of Natasha in ''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812]]'' with the [[American Repertory Theatre]]; she made her [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut when that show opened at the [[Imperial Theatre]] on November 14, 2016.<ref name='Playbill'/> She appeared on ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]'' on December 12, 2016 to discuss the role.\n\nOn television she is best known for her featured role on the second season of the [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] series, ''[[Unreal (TV series)|UnREAL]]''.<ref name='Vulture'>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2016/08/unreal-denee-benton-on-why-ruby-is-important.html|title=UnREAL\u2019s Den\u00e9e Benton on Why a Character Like Ruby Is Important and Representation in Hollywood |last1=Basti\u00e9n |first1=Angelica Jade |last2= |first2= |date=10 Aug 2016 |website=Vulture |publisher= |access-date=22 Aug 2016}}</ref><ref name='Deadline'>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/01/monica-barbaro-denee-benton-cast-unreal-season-2-lifetime-1201692977/ |title=\u2018UnReal\u2019: Monica Barbaro, Den\u00e9e Benton & More Join Season 2 Cast On Lifetime |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |last2= |first2= |date=29 Jan 2016 |website=Deadline Hollywood |publisher= |access-date=22 Aug 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn October 17, 2018, it was announced that Benton would assume the role of [[Elizabeth Schuyler Hamilton|Eliza Hamilton]] in the Broadway production of [[Hamilton (musical)|''Hamilton'']], beginning performances on October 30.<ref name=\"Broadway.com\"/>\n\n== Theatre credits ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year(s)\n!Production\n!Role\n!Location\n!Category\n|-\n|rowspan=2 |2014\u201315\n|rowspan=2 |''[[The Book of Mormon (musical)|The Book of Mormon]]''\n|rowspan=2 |Nabulungi\n|N/A\n|U.S. National Tour\n|-\n|[[Prince of Wales Theatre]]\n|West End\n|-\n|2015\u201316\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Natasha Rostova]]\n|[[American Repertory Theater]]\n|Regional, Pre-Broadway\n|-\n|2016\u201317\n|[[Imperial Theatre]]\n|Broadway\n|-\n|2017\n| ''[[Of Thee I Sing]]''\n| Mary Turner\n| [[Carnegie Hall]]\n|MasterVoices Concert\n|-\n|2018\u201319\n|[[Hamilton (musical)|''Hamilton'']]\n|[[Elizabeth Schuyler Hamilton|Eliza Hamilton]]\n|[[Richard Rodgers Theatre]]\n|Broadway\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2013\n|''The Narrative of Dalvin Reynolds''\n| Felicia \n| Short film \n|-\n|2018\n|''Mother's Milk''\n|Lark\n| \n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Friend (film)|The Friend]]''\n| Charlotte\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Unreal (TV series)|UnREAL]]''\n|Ruby Carter\n|10 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[imdbtitle:8004684|25]]''\n| Morgan\n| Television film \n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2017\n|[[Tony Award]]\n|[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical|Best Actress in a Musical]] \n| rowspan=3\" |''[[Natasha, Pierre & The Great Comet of 1812]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Drama League Award]]\n|Distinguished Performance\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Theatre World Award]]\n| {{win|Honoree}}\n|\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{R